The software, documentation and any fonts accompanying this License and contained in the corelib software package whether on disk, in read only memory, on any other media or in any other form (collectively the "Bravura Software") are licensed, not sold, to you by Bravura I/S. ("Bravura") for use only under the terms of this License, and Bravura reserves all rights not expressly granted to you. The rights granted herein are limited to Bravura's and its licensors' intellectual property rights in the Bravura Software and do not include any other patents or intellectual property rights. You own the media on which the Bravura Software is recorded but Bravura and/or Bravura's licensor(s) retain ownership of the Bravura Software itself. The Bravura Software in this package and any copies, which this License authorizes you to make, are subject to this License.


2 Definitions

2.1 Authorized Development System
"Authorized Development System" means any computer on which you are licensed to install the Bravura Software for development purposes, and that runs any version of the following operating systems:

    * FreeBSD
    * OpenBSD
    * Linux
    * Mac OS X
    * Windows XP
    * Windows Vista

2.2 Authorized Deployment System
"Authorized Deployment System" means a computer that runs an operating system that supports the Apache Webserver with mod_php and which is either owned and/or operated (i) by you for your internal and/or external web application, or (ii) by a third party as a web application service, provided that you have a written agreement with such third party that protects Bravura's interest in the Bravura Software at least to the same extent as this License.

